Peak analysis of Khd1/Hek2 CRAC data

Jing Qi Chong

9th Apr 2022

Summary

This analysis searches for motifs associated with Khd1-bound RNA from the CRAC datasets using the MEME software. This script relies on Khd1-bound peak data in gtf format file produced by pyCalculateFDRs.py software in the nf_CRACpipeline and the genome sequence in fasta format (Saccharomyces_cerevisiae.EF4.74.dna.toplevel.shortChrNames.fa) as input.

This script filter Khd1 CRAC hits (peaks) by read count, width and false dicovery rate (FDR) and then generate fasta files that contains the sequences of the filtered peaks. Lastly, the MEME software is run to search for motifs enriched in the filtered peaks.

                             )
Rsamtools::indexFa(S288C_FaF)
## class: FaFile 
## path: /Users/ew.../Saccharomyces_cerevisiae.EF4.74.dna.toplevel.shortChrNames.fa
## index: /Use.../Saccharomyces_cerevisiae.EF4.74.dna.toplevel.shortChrNames.fa.fai
## gzindex: /U.../Saccharomyces_cerevisiae.EF4.74.dna.toplevel.shortChrNames.fa.gzi
## isOpen: FALSE 
## yieldSize: NA
getSeq_gffdf <- function(gff_df,faf=S288C_FaF) {
    out_seqs <- getSeq(faf,
                       makeGRangesFromDataFrame(gff_df) )
    names(out_seqs) <- gff_df %>%
        unite("peakname", chromosome, start, end, strand, ID,sep="_") %>%
        pull(peakname)
    return(out_seqs)
}

select_seqs_above_minwidth <- function(StringSet,minwidth=10) {
    widths <- width(StringSet)
    return( StringSet[ which(widths > minwidth) ])
}

Top 500 peaks, min width 8 (more inclusive)

MEME motif search

Runs MEME motif search on top 100 peaks. We ran this with MEME 5.4.1

run_MEME <- function(fafile, outputdir, nmotifs = 10, minw = 5, maxw = 8,dry_run = FALSE) {
    cmd_meme <- paste("meme", fafile, "-dna", "-oc", outputdir, 
                      "-mod anr", "-nmotifs", nmotifs, 
                      "-minw", minw, "-maxw", maxw, 
                      "-markov_order 1", "-objfun classic")
    if (!dry_run) {
        system(cmd_meme)
    }
    cmd_meme
}
run_MEME(
        here::here("Khd1_SRR847751",
                   "MEME",
                   "Khd1_SRR847751_peaks_FDR_p0_01_desc100_minwidth20.fa"),
        here::here("Khd1_SRR847751",
                   "MEME",
                   "Khd1_SRR847751_peaks_FDR_p0_01_desc100_minwidth20_MEME"),
         dry_run = TRUE)
